This file used to contain a schema guess (customer_id, complaint_type,
etc.) written before I'd seen your actual Supabase project. That guess
doesn't match your real database and running it will throw errors like
"column customer_id does not exist" against your actual tables — so
it's been removed rather than left around to run by accident.

Your real schema already exists (profiles, complaints, complaint_categories,
maintenance_tasks, task_updates, feedback — with resident_id, category_id,
etc.). Use these two files instead, in order:

  1. seed_categories.sql   — creates the complaint categories the app expects
  2. rls-patch.sql          — Row Level Security policies written against
                              your actual column names

Run both in the Supabase SQL Editor. Safe to re-run either one.

Optional demo data (run only after customer accounts exist):

  seed_mock_billing.sql — adds six realistic monthly billing records to
                          every active customer for demonstrations and
                          screenshots. Safe to re-run without duplicating
                          the same customer/billing-period combination.

